GEORGE DEWEY v. THE UNITED STATES.

[35 C. Cls. R.;

178 U. S. R., 210.] On the claimant"1 s Appeal.

The decision of the court below (reported p. 172 ante) is affirmed on the same grounds.

Mr. Justice Harlan

delivered the opinion of the Supreme Court May 14, 1900.

 Mr. Chief Justice Fuller

delivered a dissenting opinion, in which

 Mr. Justice White and Mr. Justice McKenna

concurred.
